title: For Sale:  Savage 93R17 BTVS 17 HMR Rifle
postcontent:
This is the Savage Arms bolt action 17 HMR varmint rifle, with laminated satin finish thumbhole stock and bull barrel, in stainless steel.  It has Savage's adjustable Accu-Trigger. The thumbhole stock allows the shooter to get very close to the stock without hand interference.  It looks wild, but is very ergonomic and functional for accurate shooting.  The barrel is floated and does not contact the forend, for super accurate shooting.

Comes with original box, manual, lock, 5rd magazine, and trigger adjustment tool.  It includes a Pentax  Gameseeker 4-12x40 variable zoom scope with steel Weaver rings.  It has the bullet drop reticle, and while not a high end scope, has performed very well with this rifle.  The scope can be negotiated out of the deal, but I'd prefer that it went as a package.  I'm basically sacrificing it as part of the package deal.

The condition is like-new-in-box.  You'd be hard pressed to find any flaws in the condition.  It was only fired from a benchrest and thus never saw the rigors of being slung and carried in the field.  It's a lot of fun to shoot--I'm just changing things up in my collection.

The gun is on display (for sale) at Gilcrest Farm Supply (FFL) and can be inspected and purchased Monday-Saturday.  This is John Taylor's store in Gilcrest.  He does not charge any transfer fee other than the required $10 state fee.  While there is sales tax in Gilcrest, it's lower than the Metro area.  The lack of transfer fee, which can be $30-35-45 at most shops doing universal background checks, more than makes up for the sales tax.  In other words, if I sold you this gun out of my living room, we'd have to go to a shop and pay the store's universal BC fee plus the $10 state fee.

The price is $425.

title: For Sale:  Mosin Nagant M44 with Ammo and Accessories
postcontent:
I've decided to sell my M44 to fund a re-barrel of my main hunting rifle. The rifle was made at Izhevsk in 1944 as seen on the receiver markings. (Zastava was the closest match in the Armslist manufacturer category.) Imported by Samco as marked under the muzzle.

This is fun at the range as well as good for deer hunting in the woods up north. It's compact and quick to point with a wide sling that makes it easy to carry. The rifle is clean and well taken care of, always dried and oiled at the end of the day ever since I cleaned off the cosmoline. There's no rust on the metal and no cracks in the wood.

I mounted a weaver base in place of the rear sight and put a BSA red dot on the rail. The original sight parts are included. There are two boxes (40 rounds) of soft point brass case Winchester ammo and approx 500 rounds of surplus ammo. 440 of that is still sealed in the can.

Here's my math for what I'm asking. Prices seem to be all over the place on the rifles with an average at $200. The scope base, red dot, and case are worth $60. The Winchester white box ammo is worth $40. The can of surplus ammo is worth at least $100 since that's the lowest sale I've seen on this in the last 6 months. Let's say the remaining 60 or 70 rounds are worth $15.

Make a reasonable cash offer. Trades of long guns will be considered. No muzzleloaders, shotguns, or handguns please. I can come up with cash to even the deal if you have a 450 Bushmaster upper or complete rifle to trade.

I will deal face to face, over 21, with MI drivers license only. I will provide a signed bill of sale copy for both of our records.

postcontent:
Up for sale are 2 Axis Communications M1011-W Network Cameras. Both are in excellent condition. Both cameras include everything that comes with it: all the mounting hardware (I only used the C-clamp mounts, so the screws and wall anchors are new in bag), cd, manual and box.

These are wireless cams, so the only time you need to connect an ethernet cable is when you first connect them to your computer. After that, they can be operated wirelessly, which is how I used them. Axis makes commercial quality cams, so these aren't going to crash on you while you're on vacation (i.e., when you need them most), unlike some of the cheap consumer level cams out there.

You can set the motion detection for the areas you want to monitor and have the cam take pics and email them to you when it detects motion - the nice thing about this is that it doesn't require leaving a computer running. You can also upload pics and/or video to a hosting server on the internet, or to your own computer.

$70 each. Shipping is available. Should be pretty inexpensive to ship if you don't want the box.

title: For Sale:  EXTREMELY RARE 1984 CLAYCO SPORTS AK47
postcontent: Extremely rare 1984 Clayco Sports AK47. They are one of the earliest imports if not possibly even the first semi-auto AK47-type rifles to hit the US. This is a preban 100% Made in China by Norinco and imported before they started importing other Norincos and Polytechnology rifles. They were available with a standard fixed stock (black fiber-reinforced phenolic), or as an underfolder. The fixed stock guns were made at Ling Hua Arsenal and had polished bolts and bolt carriers. Included is the numbered matching detachable AKM style bayonet with scabbard, original cleaning kit, original mag and sling. I fired only two mags out of my AK47 many years ago and just cleaned the bore, bolt & carrier. The rest of the rifle still has the original cosmoline on some of the parts (see pics). 100% all original and numbers matching. Overall condition 98% +. The Clayco's are rumored to have been manufactured as close to Chinese military guns as possible.These Chicom rifles were featured in the September 1984 Edition of Soldier of Fortune Magazine. Included is an original 1984 Soldier of Fortune Magazine. Email me for many photos. No trades please.

I have a NEW - NEVER FIRED  Sig Sauer 556002 rifle.  This is the original Swat version.  I see many calling the rifles a swat but this is the ONLY model that has the Folding AND cooalsible stock.  Come with a pistol fore grip and flash light, a Folding and collapsible Mag Pul stock and a full length quad rail.  I purchased these under the LE program and have $1950 in them, were selling for over $2180 at on line stores  I looked around at other sites to se what they are asking and what they are selling, a new HALO is selling for $1300 - I  am pricing this at $1750 - -  I have another that I have fired about 200 rounds through and still looks new.  Will sell that one for $1650

This is a brand new Sig Sauer 556 SWAT rifle. This gun shoots the .223 Remington or the 5.56mm nato round. It has a 16" barrel with a 1:7 twist rate. It has a quad rail fore-end and flip-up front and rear sights. It comes with LED tactical flashlight that mounts into the vertical fore grip which also comes with this rifle. The gun comes standard with a factory hard case and (1) 30rd. magazine.  I have 2 extra Sig mags for this.  

 SIG 556 SWAT Like features the same high-performance two position adjustable gas piston operating rod system.  Accept standard AR / GI magazines. The SIG556 SWAT features a 16” military grade cold hammer forged barrel, chambered in 5.56mm NATO, with a twist rate of 1 in 7”.  The flash suppressor retains a standard .5 x 28 TPI thread pattern, ensuring compatibility with after-market accessories. The vented full length  tactical quad rail forearm is machined from aircraft grade aluminum alloy and hard coat anodized for durability. The quad rail features four integrated steel Picatinny rails.  The Picatinny rail equipped receiver is made of high strength carbon steel with a durable wear-resistant Nitron® finish. The rifle comes standard with the flip up combat front and rear sight system. The trigger housing is machined from an aircraft grade aluminum alloy forging with a hard-coat anodized finish designed to survive extreme conditions. The rifle comes equipped with a smooth two-stage trigger, ambidextrous safety.  A 30-round magazine is supplied with each rifle. The rifle features the MAGPUL CTR Carbine Butt stock. This butt stock is adjustable for length of pull and features a unique locking mechanism that friction locks the stock to the receiver extension for zero movement. The  pistol grip features a storage compartment. The rifle also includes the Grip-Light vertical for end grip which features a removable tactical LED flashlight and mounts directly to the quad rail for ends. It also features a folding stock with the ability to collapse, providing the best of both worlds.

I am NOT looking for trades - just wanting to thin out my collection of things I have NEVER shot and probably never will.  If you want to make a trade offer you will have to up grade me as I will have to turn around and sell what ever you give me.

This is the folder / collapsible model,  which would set you back another $250 for the folding / collapsible stock, another $210 for the fore grip and flash light, and another $250 for a full length quad rail - if you purchased them separately from sig.  (used grips are selling between $160 and $180 on ebay).  Later models did not come with these items - hence the cheaper price tag.  A HALO model with just the side folder was listed on Gun Action for $1895 and did not have to fore grip, or the quad rail and only one mag. 

After looking at Halo's, Classic and other sig rifles that are NEW, the price is fair.  I don't need the money and if you think the price is too high then buy a Halo or Classic, they are good rifles
